title: Patricia Breen Claude Monet Cliff Walk at Pourville Egg Ornament
description:
Ornament developed from Claude Monet’s Cliff Walk at Pourville, 1882, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

This limited edition Patricia Breen ornament is inspired by Claude Monet's (French, 1840-1926) painting The Cliff Walk at Pourville.   Crafted from the skillful hand of Patricia Breen in her Krakow studio, this design was produced in a limited quantity and made exclusively for the Art Institute of Chicago.

  • Dimensions: 3.54 x 2.16 diameter
  • Materials: Glass, Austrian crystals.
  • Hand painted, silvered.
  • Made in Poland.
